        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 4:54PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM EDT/354 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of
strong thunderstorms along a line extending from South Pittsburg to
near Geraldine. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cartwright, Lookout Mountain, North Chickamauga Creek Gorge, South
Pittsburg, Lakesite, Chimneys State Park, East Ridge, Red Bank,
Signal Mountain, and Middle Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
